column10: From Plane - Boarded Bus to NWDC
column12: From Plane - Boarded Bus to NWDC
column16: Observations
Only YKM flight under RPN call sign - they stopped using RPN after this flight.
No female agents, so women weren't patted down
11 women, 24 men dropped off
Records received via Yakima Air Terminal include passenger manifest with names of 15 security personnel
Approx 13 women
Picked up: 45 males, 15 females
31 men & 8 women off the plane, 11 women and 62 men on the plane. First day in new tarmac location, lot harder to see anything! No call from City Manager with a heads up.
15 women and 35 men off the plane and 16 women and 60 men on the plane
This flight wasn't observed by local YIRN members - route - San Antonio - Houston - Yakima - San Antonio
78 men and 13 women boarded the plane from the buses and 0 people got off the plane and onto the bus
71 men and 20 women deplaned and put on the bus. They only had TWO buses so there were quite a few people standing in the aisles for the 3 hour bus ride.
7 women, 60 men, several turbaned men

Buses entered through wrong gate, got to the plane late to do a count. Cliff Moore's office will share the official counts with us going forward. Pictures from Michael Collins - https://photos.app.goo.gl/tXcsok5vxh6yH499A. Buses: 15941RP, 15944RP and smaller bus 72754RP

Our count was disrupted multiple times by a Airport maintenance staff trying to talk with us to tell us we didn't know anything and that all the people on the planes were "criminals" pushing his point repeatedly. I will need to check with Cliff to see what his count was.
20 men and 10 women deplaned. This was the first time we saw three of the women able to figure out how to hold onto the hand rails, by going down the stairs sidewise.

5 women and 45 men got off the buses and onto the plane. One man got off the plane and onto the bus - there was a difference of opinion amongst observers as to whether or not he had originally been on the bus and then "rejected" by the plane crew. Buses: 5941RP and 15944RP
Mick's report: From Bus to Plane - 16 women & 73 men, total 89; from Plane to Bus - 18 women, 30 men. Cristina brought bullhorn and group of Hispanic community
62 men and 24 women off the plane, 10 women and 73 men off the bus. 15941RP, 15943RP, 15944RP
11 women and 67 men off the bus onto the plane. 1 woman deplaned and put on the bus back to Tacoma.  Buses 15941RP, 14943RP, 15944RP
Women on to small bus--18; Men onto larger bus 49. Plane was a MD83.
40 men and 20 women deplaned. No detainees boarded the plane from the buses. Buses: 15941RP and 15943RP.

4 women and 51 men off the buses onto the plane. 1 person was "rejected" and sent back to the bus.  After seeing Michael's closeup pictures it looks like one other guy got off the plane. Buses:  40272RP and 15941RP.
Off the bus and on the plane - 81 men and 7 women  --  Off the plane and on the bus - 18 women
50 men and 10 women getting off the buses ... none getting off the plane
78 men get off the plane - no women and noone off the buses. Buses: 15941RP and  15943RP
65 men and 9 women boarded the plane from the buses. 1 person got back off the plane and onto the bus. 15943RP and 40272RP
61 men and 15 women deplaned. No persons were loaded from the bus. Buses 15943RP and 15941RP.
35 men and 5 women off bus, 2 men off plane. Bus license 15941RP
Military exercises - not Allowed to view flight because exercise commander didn't want to chance his troops being photographed.
9 women and 47 men boarded the plane. No one got off the plane.  Bus license plates: 40272RP, 15941RP
63 men and 5 women off the bus and onto the plane. 12+ detainees in shirt sleeves and several in shorts!  Buses  15941RP and 15943 RP

Off the plane - 29 women and 20 men (the bunch that started out as men were mixed and it was hard to see how many were men and how many were women. and Off the buses - 6 women and 57 men. - 3 buses - 15941RP 15943 RP

12 women and 50 men got off the buses and boarded the plane.  One of the buses broke down on Valley Mall Blvd & 3rd Avenue and the first bus had to go back and pick up the detainees and came back with them 30 minutes after its first arrival. 2 men rejected on the flight and put on the bus. Bus 15943RP
4 women and 32 men off the buses. There may have been one person who was put back on a bus, but I'll awaiting the photographers pics so we can figure that out. Buses:  15943RP and 15944RP
60 men and 17 women got off the buses; 3 men got off the plane.  Buses:  15943RP, 15944RP and 72716RP
7 women and 54 men got off the bus and 2 men got off the plane.  Buses 15944RP and 14941RP

43 men and 6 women got off the bus and boarded the plane. One man was put on the plane with a wheelchair. One man got off the plane, but was then put back on. 1 bus and one lift van - for the wheelchair: License plates: 15944RP & 17508 - with wheelchair icon on license plate.
44 men and 5 women got off the buses and boarded the flight to El Paso, 2 men and 1 woman deplaned and boarded the buses to Tacoma. Licenses: 15941RP and 15943RP
Women off bus, on to plane: 11, Men off buses, on to plane: 64; 1 woman off the plane onto the bus. No Photographer.
26 men and 6 women off the buses; 1 man off the plane. No Photographer.
45 men and 6 women off the bus and boarded the plane. 1 woman off the plane. 1 turbaned man was in the group of men that got off the bus. 2 Buses. : 15943RP and smaller bus - 72716RP

Today we had 37 men get off the 2 buses and 1 man and 1 woman (I think) get off the plane. Buses:  15941RP and 15943RP. A FIRST at today's flight was that they escorted every single detainee up the steps ... we speculated it was due to icy air stairs!

column13: No restrictions. The roadway is bare and wet with slush in places
column14: Traction Tires Advised, Oversize Vehicles Prohibited. The roadway is bare and wet with slush in places
column16: 37 men and 3 women off the bus.

column13: No restrictions. The roadway is bare and wet.
column14: No restrictions. The roadway is bare and wet.
column16: 31 men and 1 women gor off the bus. No one got off the plane

column2: Very large 737 marking up the tail - no Swift Air markings on the plane at all
